```latex
\def\R1{R@xdTW}
\def\R2{R@umf3}
\def\R3{R@A9Au}
```

If you want these to behave like normal commands (usable in text/math without needing braces), you can also write:

```latex
\newcommand{\R1}{R@xdTW}
\newcommand{\R2}{R@umf3}
\newcommand{\R3}{R@A9Au}
```

